channel.description: Anyone watched fringe yesterday? :awesome: Another episode with the observers (if you watch fringe you know they are obviously based on gman) but the best part was when the observer says "[b]consequences[/b] both obvious and [b]unforeseen[/b]" and later Walter actually says [b]Unforeseen consequences[/b] almost shat bricks :smiley:

item.title: Fringe - Unforseen Consequences
item.dc:creator: waqwarrior
item.description:
Dias:

You do know that most of his appearances are in the background & can easily be missed, right? Like how G-man can be seen several times in each Half-Life game, seemingly uninvolved in everything going on.

I haven’t noticed, honestly.

Dias:

Beginning. Absolutely from the beginning. J.J. Abrams originally intended for the show to be one of those shows where you can just jump in on any given episode, but it only really works for a few episodes. He really dropped the ball in that regard. (Not that I’m complaining)

Yeah, start from the beginning. When certain plot events happen, your mind will be more blown than if you start in the middle, or even where it’s at now.

item.title: Fringe - Unforseen Consequences
item.dc:creator: waqwarrior
item.description:
toysy123:

Don’t you know that lying can lead to very serious ramifications?

Ha.

The first season of Fringe was pretty interesting, the whole Observer thing doesn’t make me think of the G-man, really, but I see where you would get that.
Decent show, but now it’s on the “Friday night death slot” on Fox, where…well, Firefly and other shows have died off not long after being put in that spot.
The last storyarc, which featured shit with the other universe, got pretty boring and dragged on and on, was pretty boring actually. Now it’s back to being pretty good overall.
